						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of a slab fixed in a niche in Virakta-maṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>In this fragmentary record dated during the reign of Kalachuri king whose name is lost, only the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> and the week-day, <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> <hi rend="bold">Paṁchami, Bṛihaspativāra,</hi> are preserved.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to refer to the construction of the temple Mūlasthāna by the chief of <hi rend="bold">Babbulēśvara</hi> (name lost) and mentions the tax-officer <hi rend="italic">(suṁkad-adhikāri)</hi> Tipparasa.</p>						

						</summary>
